# Fluff Date: 2026-02-28 17:47:08
overview:<p>The Vulture Mk III is a sixty-ton Clan OmniMech produced by Alshain Weapons on Alshain for the touman of Clan Ghost Bear. Introduced in 3109 as the next generation of the original Mad Dog first produced in 2963, the design serves primarily as a support platform for frontline formations. The Vulture Mk III achieves substantially better protection than its predecessor while maintaining the same weight class and speed profile.</p><p>Originally built exclusively for the Rasalhague Dominion, the design has since entered service with the Raven Alliance as part of Clan Snow Raven's growing touman. The Vulture Mk III's common configurations emphasize fire support and suppression roles rather than direct frontline combat, a doctrinal shift driven by heavier OmniMechs such as the Karhu assuming the primary assault role that older Mad Dog variants once filled.</p>

capabilities:<p>The Vulture Mk III builds on the proven Mad Dog platform with significant structural improvements. A Bergan Version 8.3 Endo Steel chassis paired with a Vlar 300-rated XL engine allows the sixty-ton design to reach speeds of eighty-six kilometers per hour while freeing thirty tons of pod space for weapons and equipment. Nine and a half tons of Compound 24B2 ferro-fibrous armor provide markedly better protection than the original Mad Dog, addressing one of the most frequently cited criticisms of the earlier design.</p><p>In its primary configuration, the Vulture Mk III delivers devastating long-range fire support through four LRM-20 racks split between the side torsos, backed by six extended-range medium lasers distributed across the arms and center torso. This missile-heavy loadout generates significant heat, and the twelve double heat sinks mounted on the base chassis struggle to manage sustained volleys.</p><p>The Hakkøn-Morris LAP targeting and tracking system demonstrates an unusual tendency to independently prioritize target groups, occasionally overriding MechWarrior preferences to engage higher-priority threats. Combined with the design's inherent stability and variable range targeting capability, the Vulture Mk III proves a reliable fire support platform regardless of which configuration is loaded into its pod bays.</p>

deployment:<p>A custom configuration developed for the Blessed Order's revived First Division aboard the Unending Faith III, this variant adapts the Vulture Mk III for combined-arms operations using a mix of Clan and Inner Sphere technology. Paired LRM-15 racks in each side torso provide fire support capability, while chin-turret-mounted extended-range medium lasers offer defensive coverage. An extended-range medium laser and extended-range small laser in the left arm complement an Inner Sphere Light PPC in the right arm for varied engagement ranges. Four tons of LRM ammunition sustain the missile loadout, while the inclusion of an Improved C3 Computer allows this variant to share targeting data across networked units, significantly enhancing the effectiveness of the entire formation.</p>

history:<p>The Vulture Mk III's development reflects the Rasalhague Dominion's efforts to modernize its touman with domestically produced OmniMechs. Alshain Weapons, operating from the former GK&T facility on Alshain that Clan Ghost Bear acquired during the Clan Invasion, introduced the design in 3109 as a direct successor to the original Mad Dog that had served Clan forces since 2963. The factory's heritage as an Inner Sphere facility adapted for Clan production gave the Vulture Mk III its distinctive Bergan chassis and mixed-heritage component suite.</p><p>The design quickly found favor within the Rasalhague Dominion's garrison and second-line formations, where its improved survivability over the original Mad Dog addressed longstanding complaints about that venerable design's thin armor. As Clan Ghost Bear's military doctrine evolved during the early thirty-second century, heavier frontline OmniMechs like the Karhu assumed primary assault roles, pushing the Vulture Mk III into dedicated fire support positions where its missile-heavy configurations excelled.</p><p>The Vacaville Slaughter of November 3120 demonstrated the Vulture Mk III's devastating firepower in stark terms. When dissidents on Constance fomented rebellion and murdered most of the capital's administrators, the Fifty-sixth Provisional Garrison Cluster deployed a Trinary to pacify the world. After surrounding the rebel-held Vacaville subdivision, Star Captain Jaymar ordered the Vultures, all in their primary configuration, to bombard the town. Sustained LRM barrages systematically leveled entire city quarters, illustrating both the design's destructive capability and the severity of Clan pacification doctrine.</p><p>Beyond the Rasalhague Dominion, the Vulture Mk III has seen significant adoption within the Raven Alliance, where Clan Snow Raven fields the design in growing numbers. This proliferation reflects ongoing military cooperation between the two Clan successor states, both of which share a pragmatic approach to force modernization and domestic production. The BLO custom configuration developed for the Blessed Order's revived First Division aboard the Unending Faith III represents an unusual adoption by an Inner Sphere organization, adapted with mixed Clan and Inner Sphere technology to support networked combined-arms operations.</p>

